If you are building a modern app or website, you will likely need a database. But building and managing database clusters from the ground up is time consuming. So, we built [Managed Databases](https://www.digitalocean.com/docs/databases/?utm_medium=email&utm_source=education&utm_campaign=gettingstarted) that allow you to offload the complex, mundane, and essential database administration tasks to us. Managed Databases support MongoDB, PostgreSQL, MySQL, and Redis.

What does ‘managed’ truly mean in the context of our Managed Databases?

We create the databases for you. All you have to do is specify the engine type, cluster configuration, data center, and database name.

We back them up. Our clusters are automatically backed up every day, and retained for seven days. More importantly, backups are free!

We handle security. By default, we encrypt data at rest with LUKS and in transit with SSL. We also handle software updates and security patches, which ensures your database is always up to date.

We make your databases highly available. Just add standby nodes to your cluster and create clusters that are highly available. Traffic failover happens automatically and immediately, meaning your apps won’t lose business continuity—and you can use standby nodes for read-only queries.

We reduce latency. Easily serve global users with reduced latency via read-only nodes, which are replicas of the primary node in additional geographical regions.

[Get started](http://cloud.digitalocean.com/databases?utm_medium=email&utm_source=education&utm_campaign=gettingstarted) and spin up database clusters with just a few clicks and create a fully-managed, production-ready database cluster, no matter the skill level.

